The Nigerian Meteorological Agency (NiMet) has predicted cloudy and sunny weather conditions with thunderstorms and rainfall over most part of Nigeria on Monday.  NiMet’s Weather Outlook on Sunday in Abuja predicted partly cloudy to sunny conditions over the central cities in the morning. It added that sunny conditions were anticipated over the region later in the afternoon and evening with day and night temperatures of 27 to 36 and 12 to 24 degrees Celsius, respectively. The agency predicted that the Northern States would experience sunny conditions throughout the forecast period with day and night temperatures of 33 to 38 and 10 to 20 degrees Celsius, respectively. According to NiMet, Southern States will experience partly cloudy to cloudy conditions with chances of scattered thunderstorm over Calabar, Eket and Uyo in the morning. “Partly cloudy conditions are likely over the inland with prospects of scattered thunderstorms over Lagos, Portharcourt and Calabar during the afternoon and evening hours with day and night temperatures of 31 to 34 and 20 to 24 degrees Celsius, respectively. “Sunny and partly cloudy conditions are expected over the North, the central and the inland cities with chances of scattered thunderstorms over some parts of the coastal region in the next 24 hours,” NiMet predicted.